wikipedia_page.main: William Leader (19 October 1767 – 18 January 1828) was a British Member of Parliament for Camelford and WinchelseaHe represented Camelford from 1812 to 1818, and Winchelsea from 1823 to 1826.His son John Temple Leader (1810–1903), and his nephew William Leader Maberly (1798–1885) were also MPs.His grave is in Putney Old Burial Ground.
